Sentencas: Application of (Sm0.5Sr0.5)CoO3 as a cathode material on Zr0.89Sc0.1Ce0.01O1.95 electrolyte for reduced-temperature operation solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) was investigated in detail.
Titulo: Application of (Sm0.5Sr0.5)CoO3 as a cathode material to (Zr,Sc)O2 electrolyte with ceria-based interlayers for reduced-temperature operation SOFCs

Sentencas: As a protective layer for preventing the unfavorable solid-state reactions between materials, doped ceria thin films with an apparent density range between 50 and 80% were fabricated on the electrolyte by a cost-effective wet ceramic process using nanometer (Ce0.8Sm0.2)O-1.9 and submicrometer (Ce0.9Gd0.1)O-1.95 powders.
Titulo: Application of (Sm0.5Sr0.5)CoO3 as a cathode material to (Zr,Sc)O2 electrolyte with ceria-based interlayers for reduced-temperature operation SOFCs

Sentencas: The impact of doped ceria interlayers on the performance of (Sm0.5Sr0.5)CoO3 cathode was investigated by X-ray diffraction and ac impedance measurements.
Titulo: Application of (Sm0.5Sr0.5)CoO3 as a cathode material to (Zr,Sc)O2 electrolyte with ceria-based interlayers for reduced-temperature operation SOFCs

Sentencas: It was found that controlling the microstructure of interlayers is important for (Sm0.5Sr0.5)CoO3 cathodic performance.
Titulo: Application of (Sm0.5Sr0.5)CoO3 as a cathode material to (Zr,Sc)O2 electrolyte with ceria-based interlayers for reduced-temperature operation SOFCs

Sentencas: The (Sm0.5Sr0.5)CoO3 cathode deposited on Zr0.89Sc0.1Ce0.01O1.95 electrolyte coated by (Ce0.8Sm0.2)O-1.9 or (Ce0.9Gd0.1)O-1.95 interlayer can reach an interface conductivity of 4.4 or 7.2 S/cm(2), respectively, at 700 degrees C. (c) 2006 The Electrochemical Society.
Titulo: Application of (Sm0.5Sr0.5)CoO3 as a cathode material to (Zr,Sc)O2 electrolyte with ceria-based interlayers for reduced-temperature operation SOFCs
